hands_on_practices.solution:
1.  Energy and angular momentum    
   $$E=-\frac{G M\mu}{2a},\quad 
     L=\mu\sqrt{GMa(1-e^2)}\,. $$    
2.  Fluxes (Peters 1964)    
   $$\Bigl\langle\frac{dE}{dt}\Bigr\rangle
     =-\frac{32}{5}\frac{G^4M^2\mu^2}{c^5a^5}f(e),\quad
     \Bigl\langle\frac{dL}{dt}\Bigr\rangle
     =-\frac{32}{5}\frac{G^{7/2}M^{3/2}\mu^2}{c^5a^{7/2}}g(e).$$    
3.  Semi‐major‐axis decay    
   $$\frac{dE}{dt}=\frac{G M\mu}{2a^2}\frac{da}{dt}
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     \frac{da}{dt}
     =-\frac{64}{5}\frac{G^3M\mu}{c^5a^3}f(e).$$    
4.  Eccentricity decay (Peters 1964)    
   $$\frac{de}{dt}
     =-\frac{304}{15}\,e\,\frac{G^3M\mu}{c^5a^4}\,\frac{1+\tfrac{121}{304}e^2}{(1-e^2)^{5/2}}\,.
$$    
5.  Timescales and ratio for $e\ll1$ (keep leading order)    
   $$\tau_a=-\frac{a}{da/dt}
     =\frac{5}{64}\frac{c^5a^4}{G^3M\mu},\qquad
     \tau_e=-\frac{e}{de/dt}
     =\frac{15}{304}\frac{c^5a^4}{G^3M\mu},$$    
   $$\frac{\tau_e}{\tau_a}
     =\frac{\tfrac{15}{304}}{\tfrac{5}{64}}
     =\frac{15\cdot64}{304\cdot5}
     =\frac{12}{19}\,. $$
